505
00:20:39,380 --> 00:20:41,880
As the bourgeois economy
was becoming dominant,

506
00:20:41,900 --> 00:20:46,400
they discard the "political" part to give
Economics an alleged neutrality.

507
00:20:46,470 --> 00:20:48,610
“No, no. Economics
has nothing to do with Politics.

508
00:20:48,740 --> 00:20:49,890
Economics is Economics.

509
00:20:50,110 --> 00:20:51,170
It is an exact science,

510
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:53,530
we conduct a study of reality neutrally."

511
00:20:53,590 --> 00:20:55,070
And for Marxists,

512
00:20:55,110 --> 00:20:57,880
until this day the expression used is
"Political Economy", OK?

513
00:20:57,930 --> 00:21:02,690
Marxists don't disassociate
the economy from politics. Ever.

514
00:21:02,730 --> 00:21:04,870
By the way,
I even put here, look.

515
00:21:05,080 --> 00:21:08,740
For those who don't know,
Marx's masterpiece “Capital”,

516
00:21:08,820 --> 00:21:09,600
“Das Kapital”

517
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:12,800
it says here:
“A Critique of Political Economy”,

518
00:21:12,850 --> 00:21:16,030
“Capital: Critique of Political Economy",
it's the subtitle.

519
00:21:16,050 --> 00:21:18,690
So, the Marxist economy develops out

520
00:21:18,730 --> 00:21:22,450
of a critique of the political economy
