1456
01:04:08,740 --> 01:04:13,340
This book is a book that is even good
to read as Lenin's first book, too.

1457
01:04:13,410 --> 01:04:13,840
Why?

1458
01:04:13,840 --> 01:04:16,820
Here, Lenin talks about
the role of the State in a revolution

1459
01:04:16,850 --> 01:04:19,300
— Much like what Marx does
in the Critique of the Gotha Program —

1460
01:04:19,300 --> 01:04:21,740
talking about what is
the role of the State in a revolution,

1461
01:04:21,770 --> 01:04:23,740
how the working class
should manage the State,

1462
01:04:23,740 --> 01:04:25,420
what is it for;
and what is the State,

1463
01:04:25,420 --> 01:04:26,840
he theorizes about the State, too.

1464
01:04:26,890 --> 01:04:28,360
This book here,
if you're going to read it,

1465
01:04:28,420 --> 01:04:30,780
